claim.claim-text:
1. A computerized method of locating and opening a file on a computer, said computer including an index containing metadata associated with one or more files stored on the computer or on an external source, said metadata identifying a type of each of the one or more files, said method comprising:
initiating a current application on the computer;
initiating a desktop search application on the computer, said initiating the desktop search application comprising:
displaying to a user of the computer a persistent first user interface (UI) element that is persistently available to a user of the computer by being located in an operating system shell of an operating system of the computer, said persistent first UI element including a search field for receiving a user-entered dynamically modifiable search term, said search term comprising one or more characters representative of a file to be opened on the computer, said search term being dynamically modifiable as the user enters additional characters, wherein each file is indexed according to the file type identified in the metadata associated with the file;
dynamically modifying the user-entered dynamically modifiable search term as the user enters one or more search operators to the search term;
dynamically defining a scope of the index of files to be searched based on the user-entered dynamically modifiable search term, wherein the scope of the index is dynamically modified as the one or more search term search operators are dynamically modified;
in response to the received dynamically modifiable search term, dynamically searching the index of files by file type, as identified by the metadata associated with each file, and based on the defined scope of the index according to the dynamically modified search term;
generating search results in response to searching the metadata associated with each file based on the dynamically modified search term, said generated search results having a plurality of files having a plurality of types;
dynamically filtering the generated search results according to each type of file listed in the search results; and
displaying a second UI element associated with the first persistent UI element, said second UI element including a window for displaying the filtered search results based on the scope of the index, said second UI element receiving user input to select the file to be opened from the filtered search results, and wherein said computer is responsive to said user input via the second UI element for opening the selected file.

12. A computer-readable storage medium having computer-executable instructions for a desktop search program for locating and opening a file on a computer, said computer including an index containing metadata representative of one or more files stored on the computer or on an external source, said metadata identifying a type associated with each of the one or more files associated with the one or more applications, said computer-readable medium comprising:
a persistent component responsive to a search term received from a user for processing a query, said query comprising one or more characters representative of a desired file on the computer to be opened, said query being dynamically modified as the user enters additional characters and search operators, said persistent component listing the one or more characters and search operators in a user interface element for receiving the query from the user, said persistent component being persistently available to the user of the computer by being located in an operating system shell of an operating system of the computer, said user interface element residing in a taskbar of the operating system of the computer;
an index component called by the persistent component for creating a query object with the query received from the user and creating a connection to the search index to query for metadata associated with a file as a function of the query;
a current application component dynamically defining a scope of the index as the query is being dynamically modified with one or more search operators as the user enters additional characters, wherein said query is repeated as each of the one or more characters and search operators is input to the user interface element; and
a query component called by the index component for querying the dynamically defined scope of the index according to the created query object, wherein the scope of the index is dynamically modified as the query is dynamically modified;
wherein said query component generates search results in response to the querying and the determining of the query object, said generated search results having a plurality of files having a plurality of types, wherein the query component further dynamically filters the generated search results according to each type of file listed in the generated search results;
an execution component responsive to a user selection of a file from the filtered search results based on the scope of the index, and said execution component for fetching metadata for the selected item for displaying in an user interface element.

15. A computerized method comprising:
displaying to a user of a computer a persistent first user interface (UI) element that is persistently available to the user of the computer by being located in an operating system shell of an operating system of the computer, said persistent first UI element being presented on the desktop of the computer via a display of the computer, said persistent first UI element including a search field for receiving a user-entered dynamically modifiable search term, said computer including an index containing metadata representative of one or more applications installed thereon, said index further containing metadata representative of the one or more files associated with the one or more applications stored on the computer or on an external source;
dynamically modifying the user-entered dynamically modifiable search term by dynamically modifying one or more search term operators;
executing a desktop searching application for dynamically defining a scope of the index based on dynamically modifying the user-entered search term operators, said executed desktop searching application searching for the one or more files, based on the defined scope of the index, wherein the scope of the index is dynamically modified as the search term is dynamically modified;
in response to the received dynamically modifiable search term, dynamically searching the dynamically defined scope of the index based on the dynamically modified search term, and accessing, by the persistent UI element, the index to dynamically search the metadata associated with the index based on the dynamically modified search term;
generating search results in response to the searching of the metadata and the determining based on the dynamically modified search term, said generated search results having a plurality of files having a plurality of types, wherein the metadata identifies a file type, said file type associated with each of the one or more files;
dynamically filtering the generated search results according to the metadata for each type of file listed in the search results; and
displaying a second UI element associated with the first persistent UI element to the user via the display of the computer, said second UI element including a window for displaying filtered results of searching, said second UI element receiving user input to select one or more files to be opened from the filtered search results, and wherein said computer is responsive to user input via the second UI element for opening the selected file.
